-----------------------------------------------------------------
-------------------------------------------------------------------
          --- Escape Code Used in Shell Prompts ---
-------------------------------------------------------------------
-----------------------------------------------------------------


=================================================================
   SEQUENCE    |    ACTION
---------------|------------------------------------------------
               |
  \033[{n}J    | ( J: screen )
               |
   \033[0J     | Clears from cursor until end of screen
   \033[1J     | Clears from cursor to beginning of screen
   \033[2J     | Clears entire screen
               |
---------------|------------------------------------------------
               |
  \033[{n}K    | ( K: line )
               |
   \033[0K     | Clears from cursor until end of line
   \033[1K     | Clears from cursor to beginning of line
   \033[2K     | Clears entire line
               |
=================================================================


================================
  KEY-CODES  |  DESCRIPTION
-------------|-----------------
   \033[A    |   Cursor Up
-------------|-----------------
   \033[B    |  Cursor Down
-------------|-----------------
   \033[C	 |  Cursor Right
-------------|-----------------
   \033[D	 |  Cursor Left
================================


=============================================================================
 SEQUENCE  |  VALUE DISPLAYED 
-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
    \a     | ASCII bell. Audible beep emits when encountered
-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
    \d     | Current Day Month Date format (Mon May 26)
-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
    \h     | Hostname of the local machine minus the trailing domain name
-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
    \H     | Full hostname
-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
    \j     | Number of jobs running in the current shell session
-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
    \l     | Name of the current terminal device
-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
    \n     | A newline character
-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
    \r     | A carriage return
-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
    \s     | Name of the shell program
-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
    \t     | Current time in 24-hour format [ hours:minutes:seconds ]
-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
    \T     | Current time in 12-hour format 
-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
    \@     | Current time in 12-hour AM/PM format
-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
    \A     | Current time in 24-hour format [ hours:minutes ]
-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
    \u     | Username of the current user
-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
    \v     | Version number of the shell
-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
    \V     | Version and release numbers of the shell
-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
    \w     | Name of the current working directory
-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
    \W     | Last part of the current working directory name
-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
    \!     | History number of the current command
-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
    \#     | Number of commands entered during this shell session
-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
    \$     | This displays a "$" char unless we have sudo privileges, then #
-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
    \[     | Used to manipulate the terminal emulator in some way
-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
    \]     | Signals the end of a non-printing character sequence
=============================================================================

